<img width="750" height="750" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?fit=750%2C750&amp;ssl=1" class="webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image" alt="Watch Out For ConWare – Mac Geek Gab 988 episode image" style="display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%;" link_thumbnail="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?w=3000&amp;ssl=1 3000w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=1536%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=2048%2C2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=600%2C600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=230%2C230&amp;ssl=1 230w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=160%2C160&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?resize=50%2C50&amp;ssl=1 50w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/conware-mgg988.jpg?w=2250&amp;ssl=1 2250w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /><p>Kicking off this week&#8217;s Mac Geek Gab, Dave Hamilton and Pilot Pete share a listener&#8217;s clever suggestion about storing receipts and user manuals in the Books app, a novel way to keep things organized and easily accessible.</p>
<p>Your two favorite geeks then explore the little-known trick of shrinking the picture-in-picture screen on Microsoft Teams using a trackpad, as well as a hidden feature in iOS and iPadOS that brings text on a photo to life, simply by long-pressing on it.</p>
<p>Dave and Pilot Pete also tackle troubleshooting tricks for Safari issues, spanning from the basics of uninstalling and reinstalling, to the more intricate reasons that may prevent a user from logging into websites or staying logged in. They ponder the likelihood of Safari being set to private browsing mode or having the &#8220;block all cookies&#8221; setting turned on, providing a comprehensive guide for the perplexed.</p>
<p>The dynamic duo further discuss the intricacies of using eSIMs and physical SIMs, shedding light on the potential use of multiple active eSIMs across different iPhone models.</p>
<p>Cool Stuff Found finds Dave and Pete sharing reviews of the Logitech G PowerPlay system for Qi-compatible mice and the Zenz Liberty, a versatile wireless charging pad that caters to a range of devices, including the Apple Watch. They further endorse the Eve Weather sensor as a dependable, Thread-connected weather station and the Brilliant smart home control system, which seamlessly integrates with HomeKit and devices like Sonos.</p>
<p>Wrapping it up, Dave shares his recent experience with the iOttie Velox Mini MagSafe air vent mount, a handy gadget for the car that utilizes a MagSafe connector to charge phones on-the-go. They wholeheartedly recommend this device to their listeners for its practicality and convenience. Press play, enjoy, and Don&#8217;t Get Caught!</p>
